From Blaine Gardner Subject Re FJ Owners Tankbag Suggestions Wanted In article A Mark Wallace writes Blaine Gardner writes In article A Mar Marten writes I am looking for a new tank bag now, and I wondered if you, as follow FJ owners, could make some suggestions as to what has, and has With the FJ's large, flat gas tank, I'd imagine that almost anything would work Personally, I'm quite happy with my Eclipse standard tank bag I think the only thing to watch for is the number of attachment straps Most come with and some with , I have a Bagman strap tankbag and because the rear of the tank is so narrow the fit is not optimal Good point, I'd overlooked that The Eclipse has a point mount, at the rear and at the front, and it's very stable on the FJ I have seen some with harnesses that mount to the sides of the tank, and that would be a real problem on the FJ Blaine Gardner Evans Sutherland